Clinton has
to demonstrate that she is able
to generate

29:45.217 --> 29:53.091 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
enthusiasm, intensity, passion.
I think she
has to win decisively there, no
more four-point,

29:53.191 --> 29:56.361 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
five-point victories, a la
Nevada.

29:56.461 --> 29:59.998 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And cutting right
into Super
Tuesday, which is just a few
days away.

30:00.098 --> 30:01.900 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
MARK SHIELDS: Yes. That's right.

30:02.000 --> 30:04.469 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Ramesh, how do
you see the
Democratic -- the challenge both
that Secretary

30:04.569 --> 30:06.405 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Clinton and Senator Sanders
face?

30:06.505 --> 30:10.142 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
RAMESH PONNURU: Well, the
problem for Senator
Sanders is not just that he is
so far behind

30:10.242 --> 30:15.914 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
