is behind
because he's not doing well with
African-Americans.

30:16.014 --> 30:20.919 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And that is a sign of his great
weakness in
these primary contests. You
can't win the

30:21.019 --> 30:25.057 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Democratic nomination if you
can't get a lot
of African-American votes.

30:25.157 --> 30:30.262 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The problem for Hillary Clinton
is that there's
no putting Senator Sanders away.
That is,

30:30.362 --> 30:36.401 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I think he got into the race as
a cause candidate,
as somebody who wanted to make a
point. And

30:36.501 --> 30:41.306 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
